{
    "title": "LogicInsight - Nutanix Audit",
    "description": "### **üìä LogicInsight - Nutanix Audit Dashboard Explanation**\n\nThe **LogicInsight - Nutanix Audit Events Dashboard** provides a centralized view of **security, virtual machine, and storage-related audit logs** collected across Nutanix environments. It allows administrators to **track user actions, VM lifecycle events, and system-level activities**, ensuring full visibility and traceability for operational and compliance purposes.\n\n***\n\n## **1Ô∏è‚É£ Login Audit (Blue Section - Left)**\n\nThis section tracks **user login activities** from different endpoints:\n\n-   **Login Events Panel** ‚Äì Lists all login attempts, including:\n\n    -   Source cluster and host.\n    -   Affected entity (e.g., user account).\n    -   Timestamp and event UUID.\n    -   Information if logins are successful or failed.\n\n‚úî **Why Is It Important?**\\\nEnables auditing of **user authentication patterns**, **potential security breaches**, and **suspicious login behavior**.\n\n***\n\n## **2Ô∏è‚É£ VM Audit (Purple Section - Center)**\n\nThis section covers a wide range of **virtual machine lifecycle operations**:\n\n-   **VM Migrate** ‚Äì Shows details of VM live migrations, including source and target.\n-   **VM Update** ‚Äì Tracks configuration changes applied to VMs.\n-   **VM Create** ‚Äì Logs creation of new VMs with metadata like entity UUID and hostname.\n-   **VM Delete** ‚Äì Indicates when VMs are deleted, including the initiator and type.\n\n‚úî **Why Is It Important?**\\\nTracks changes and operations on VMs to **ensure proper governance, traceability, and audit readiness**.\n\n***\n\n## **3Ô∏è‚É£ System Action (Green Section - Right)**\n\nThis panel displays **system-level activities** performed automatically or via policy:\n\n-   **Replication Events** ‚Äì Captures replication of VM recovery points (e.g., scheduled backups).\n-   **Success Audits** ‚Äì Details for each successful system action, including VM name, recovery type, source and destination node, and cluster name.\n\n‚úî **Why Is It Important?**\\\nProvides a clear audit trail of **data protection actions**, **replication health**, and **system automation success**.\n\n***\n\n## **4Ô∏è‚É£ Volume Audit (Purple Section - Bottom)**\n\nThis section logs activities related to **volume group management**:\n\n-   **Volume Create** ‚Äì Tracks the creation of volume groups, including associated tasks and metadata like `volume_group_name`, `uuid`, etc.\n\n‚úî **Why Is It Important?**\\\nEnsures proper monitoring of **storage configuration changes**, helping maintain consistency and storage governance.\n\n***\n\n### **üìå Why This Dashboard Matters?**\n\n‚úÖ **Complete Audit Trail** ‚Äì Captures all user actions, system operations, and changes across VMs and volumes.\\\n‚úÖ **Security and Compliance** ‚Äì Assists in **compliance reporting** and **security investigations**.\\\n‚úÖ **Operational Transparency** ‚Äì Enables quick diagnosis of issues by providing context for recent changes or failures.\\\n‚úÖ **Proactive Monitoring** ‚Äì Helps correlate user activity with system behavior for **faster root cause analysis**.",
